long-term chances of survival. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
<P>
   COMPUTER-VIRUS (San Francisco) _ Large corporations worldwide
scrambled to halt the spread of a malicious computer program that
began infecting computers in Israel on Monday and spread rapidly to
Europe and the U.S., carried by e-mail. The program, a computer
attack known as a worm, destroys documents created by several
widely used Microsoft programs.
