<P>
   BKN-KNICKS (New York) _ They are now one of the great teams of
the Garden, one of the epic teams of New York. The Eastern
Conference banner will hang from the beams, but what really matters
is the sound, the emotion of that Friday night in June, forever
trapped under the rafters. By George Vecsey.
</P>
<P>
   SOC-CUP-NORWAY (Hyannis, Mass.) _ The 1999 world soccer
championship begins next weekend, and Norway is taking no chances
that it will be caught off guard in defending its title by either
the heat or the time difference in the United States. By Jere
Longman.
</P>
<P>
   SOC-CUP-USA (Undated) _ No one ever wants to lose, especially
the U.S. women's soccer team, but some defeats can be instructive
and revelatory. A 1-0 defeat to Norway in the semifinals of the
1995 Women's World Cup was a short-term calamity but a long-term
benefit. By Jere Longman.
</P>
<P>
   SOC-CUP-LILLY (Undated) _ On Kristine Lilly, captain of Team
USA. By George Vecsey.
