u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ALMANAC-ON-WEB-NYTR &LR;      06-12 0322
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ALMANAC-ON-WEB-NYTR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WORLD ALMANAC MATERIAL TO GO ON THE WEB 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 By RON TRUJILLO   
 Santa Barbara (Calif.) News-Press   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   SANTA BARBARA, Calif. _ ExperTelligence, a high-tech firm based
here, has attracted a century-old, low-tech information source to
the Web.
</P>
<P>
   ExperTelligence's WebData.com _ a collection of more than 3,000
databases on the Internet _ has agreed to an exclusive deal with
The World Almanac, the 130-year-old encyclopedia publisher. About
half of the encyclopedia's information, including graphics and
photographs, will be available on WebData. com (www. WebData.com),
company officials said.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's an incredible collection of data ... very
educational-oriented,'' said Denison Bollay, president and chief
executive officer of ExperTelligence. ``And there will be a lot of
transformation from the book (encyclopedia) version to the Web.''
</P>
<P>
   WebData's encyclopedia connection _ available through an
encyclopedia icon, keyword searches or numerous other ways _ will
ease ``knowledge workers and fact finders'' with information, said
Robert Reali, executive vice president of ExperTelligence.
</P>
<P>
   The free searches will begin this summer, Reali said.
</P>
<P>
   ``The World Almanac has been providing authoritative up-to-date,
high-quality information and we think there's a great fit between
what World Almanac and WebData.com can offer to information
seekers,'' said Robert Famighetti, vice president and editorial
director of PRIMEDIA Reference Inc., the publisher of the
encyclopedia.
</P>
<P>
   Financial terms of the deal were not released. But both
companies will benefit from banner advertising, with revenue
increasing on the number of ``hits'' _ or visitors _ to the
encyclopedia connection on WebData.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Ron Trujillo writes for the Santa Barbara News-Press, Santa
Barbara, Calif., which is part of The New York Times Regional
Newspaper Group.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-12-99 1359EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
