<P>
   BUSH _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush makes his first out-of-state
trip as a presidential explorer. Iowa and New Hampshire are eager
to meet him in person. We pose the questions of how much his
delayed campaigning has hurt him and whether there's any backlash
for Bush not announcing he's a candidate. After all, he's raised
more money and is higher in the polls than any other GOP candidate.
How much more exploring does Bush need to do? When does he simply
appear indecisive? (Greenberger, Austin American-Statesman). 25-30.
