   NATION
</P>
<P>
   FAULDER-ADVANCE _ GLADEWATER, Texas _ Joseph Stanley Faulder,
61, is scheduled for execution after 7 p.m. EDT Thursday for the
July 8, 1975 slaying of Inez Phillips in her Gladewater, Texas,
home. Faulder is a native of Canada, and if the Thursday death
penalty is carried out he will become the first Canadian executed
in the United States since 1952. Gladewater residents talk about
Inez Phillips _ ``It really shook up the whole town, because she
was so beloved and so innocent'' _ in a story that advances the
Faulder execution. (Graham, Longview News-Journal). 24. WITH
PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   OLY-IOC-PREVIEW _ Olympic organizers in Salt Lake and Sydney
have told IOC members not to expect to be treated royally at their
Games, as the members are accustomed to. Several candidates to host
the 2006 Winter Games fear that they haven't had a chance to
``sell'' their cities because of a travel restriction for members.
In many small ways, the Salt Lake City scandal has changed the way
the Olympics does business. Advancing big IOC meetings in Seoul.
(Turner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 50.
