<P>
   IRAQ-SANCTIONS _ KURDISTAN, Iraq _ A review of the long-standing
economic sanctions against Iraq, now that the U.N. is doing the
most extensive review of them to date. The result is that the
sanctions are ruining the schools and killing children, but not
stopping the police from getting new cars or stopping the
construction of the Saddam Hussein Mosque, the biggest in the
world. Developing.
</P>
<P>
   (Kaplow, Cox News Service). 30. WITH PHOTOS and MAP. MOVED
Tuesday in (i) International and (k) Commentary categories.
</P>
