<P>
   BBO-BASESTEALER _ MACON, Ga. _ Just like it once did for Vince
Coleman, 73-year-old Luther Williams Field begins to buzz with
anticipation every time Rafael Furcal reaches first base.
``Everyone knows he's going to try to steal,'' longtime Macon fan
Joe Jones, 75, said of Furcal. ``I really think he's even faster
than Coleman was back then.'' Coleman stole 145 bases for Macon in
1983, setting a record for Organized Baseball. Furcal, the Atlanta
Braves' leadoff man and shortstop of the future, isn't likely to
match that. But the 18-year-old Dominican is on pace to become the
first minor or major-league player this decade to steal 100 bases
in a season. (Curtright, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25. WITH
PHOTOS.
