<P>
   GLF-PINEHURST _ When the Open returns to the South for the first
time since 1976, it will be held for the first time at Pinehurst,
N.C., one of the nation's best courses. So why the wait? Simple.
Until the course went to Bent grass, it couldn't get the greens
fast and hard enough to meet U.S. Open specifications. (Sheeley,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   WITH GLF-TIGER _ He has the skills, no question about it. If
Tigers Woods gets hot, he has the ability to run away with the U.S.
Open this week at Pinehurst, N.C. But Woods knows he must have the
right mental attitude to make it happen. In previous Opens, he has
lived and died with the go-for-it mentality on every shot. With
high rough, slick and crowned greens, that style doesn't work.
(Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
