<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NY-GIULIANI-MSRCLINTON-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GIULIANI SUGGESTS MRS. CLINTON IS NOT A KNICKS FAN 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Pressing his home-court advantage, Mayor Rudolph
Giuliani said Saturday that he assumed Hillary Rodham Clinton, a
likely future adversary for the U.S. Senate, was a Chicago Bulls
fan.
</P>
<P>
   With the New York Knicks poised to play the San Antonio Spurs in
the National Basketball Association finals Wednesday, it was the
mayor's turn for a spin move outside St. Sylvester's Roman Catholic
Church on Staten Island, where he went to celebrate the Feast of
St. Anthony and march in a parade for the 12th-century Portuguese
saint.
</P>
<P>
   And fittingly, he held a basket _ this one of white wicker, full
of bread that had been blessed and that is customarily shared on
the saint's feast day.
</P>
<P>
   As he distributed the bread to a cluster of skeptical reporters,
he was asked, ``Is Hillary Clinton a Knicks fan?''
</P>
<P>
   Finding a lane open, Giuliani drove to the basket. ``Everything
is now changing,'' he said. ``Soon we'll find out that she played
for the Brooklyn Dodgers.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
