<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following sports
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
June 13 and thereafter. For questions about stories, resends or
inquiries, call Eddie Ibardolasa at (818) 713-3602. 
 
 
BBO-DODGERS-ATHLETICS (Oakland) _ The Los Angeles Dodgers face the
Oakland A's at 1:05 p.m. PDT. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
GEN-CROUSE-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Column on women athletes who are
stalked. 
By Karen Crouse. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BKN-LAKERS (Los Angeles) _ Update on Los Angeles Lakers' coaching
situation. 
By Howard Beck. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
SOC-WORLDCUP (Los Angeles) _ Impact of the Women's World Cup on the
Los Angeles area, compared to the 1994 Men's World Cup. 
San Gabriel Valley Tribune. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
SOC-GALAXY-FIRE (Pasadena, Calif.) _ The Los Angeles Galaxy faces
the Chicago Fire at 7:30 p.m. PDT. 
By Fred J. Robledo/San Gabriel Valley Tribune. (Will move on the
``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBO-BASEBALL-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Weekly baseball column, on
early success of the Arizona Diamondbacks. 
By Matt McHale. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBA-DISARCINA (Los Angeles) _ Feature on Anaheim Angels shortstop
Gary DiSarcina, who is about to begin rehab from a broken arm
suffered in spring training. 
By Matt McHale. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
