   NL EAST
</P>
<P>
   Counsell, Marlins break up
</P>
<P>
   If you can't find playing time in Florida, someone is sending a
message, which second baseman Craig Counsell has received loud and
clear. After being lifted Tuesday for defensive substitute Luis
Castillo, Counsell, a hero of the 1997 world champion Marlins,
requested a meeting with manager John Boles and asked to be traded.
Friday, he was designated for assignment.
</P>
<P>
   ``I can handle being a utility player, and I can handle losing
my job in spring training,'' said Counsell, who lost the starting
job to Castillo during camp. ``But now they're telling me I can't
play defense?'' Dave Dombrowski . . .
</P>
<P>
   Phillies right-hander Carlton LoewerPhillip Marone ordered an
MRI that an incomplete stress fracture was found above the elbow.
Marone's discovery saved Loewer from possibly snapping his arm, as
Tampa Bay's Tony SaundersNL CENTRALA vote against interleagueMark
McGwireWith the old park jammed with 20,000 just to watch batting
practice, McGwire marveled, ``If I hit a home run, they cheer for
me. And if I strike out, they cheer for me again.''
</P>
<P>
   Beyond that, interleague play has lost its interest for the
Cardinals, who urge that it should be revamped on a rotating
divisional basis or scrapped. Growing familiarity and the imbalance
between divisions mar the current arrangement.
</P>
