knowledge, but he said the penalties for such violations do little
to discourage the practice.
</P>
<P>
   ``In my opinion, the penalties for Hazmat violations amount to
little more than hand slaps and fines,'' he said, ``which only
encourages the bold and the reckless to try shipping the high
tariff dangerous goods without telling the shipper.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
