<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Sunday,
June 13, 1999. If you have any questions, please call Miranda
Kennedy or Patricia Hardin on the Star's News Desk at (816)
234-4720.
</P>
<P>
   MURDERS-DECADE (KANSAS CITY, Mo.) _ Ten years ago, three young
Kansas women vanished, never to be seen or heard from again. The
secret of their fate remains locked away in a prison cell, along
with the man who has kept it to himself for a decade. His
prediction to police, ``You'll dig them up,'' remains unfulfilled.
Despite the lack of bodies, Richard Grissom Jr. was convicted of
murdering all three. By TONY RIZZO. Story will move in the ``a''
category.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-FESTIVAL (OLEAN, Mo.) _ Last Saturday Olean's numbers
jumped to 6,000 as throngs of people jammed this village for its
festival. There was the smell of cooking -- which organizers freely
admitted was aimed at snagging as many visitors as possible. In the
deep fryers were turkey fries and bull fries -- what some call
mountain oysters. In short, the main course was that part of
poultry and livestock rarely mentioned but which some find a
culinary delicacy. By JIM FISHER. Story will move in the ``a''
category.
</P>
<P>
   CHARTER-SCHOOLS (KANSAS CITY, Mo.) _ Kansas City's new charter
school experiment is the most aggressive in the nation. That has
parents and educators both excited and worried. By PHILIP O'CONNOR.
Story will move in the ``a'' category.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-IOWA _ Saturday visit by Texas Gov. George W. Bush to Iowa.
Developing. By STEVE KRASKE. Story will move in the ``a'' category.
</P>
<P>
   PRIVATE-CITY (KANSAS CITY, Mo.) _ A look at the trend toward
privatization of city services. Developing. With four sidebars:
PRIVATE-WATER, PRIVATE-ARENA, PRIVATE-PORT and PRIVATE-GOLF. By
LYNN HORSLEY. Story will move in the ``a'' category.
</P>
<P>
   GUSEWELLE-COLUMN (Undated) _ U.S. 71 makes your java jump. By
C.W. GUSEWELLE. Story will move in the ``k'' category.
</P>
