<P>
   &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) _ Seventy-seven-year-old Bob Deheer was
arrested at the local VA hospital for trying to park in a spot
reserved for VIPs. Deheer was a machine-gunner in France in World
War II. During an enemy assault in the fall of 1944, another gunner
abandoned his weapon and Deheer took over and helped fight off the
attack. He was awarded the Bronze Star and the Purple Heart. If
that doesn't make him a VIP, what does? By E.J. MONTINI. Story will
move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories.
</P>
