</P>
<P>
   and maintaining old ones.
</P>
<P>
   12. THE WHITE HOUSE CONNECTION, by Jack Higgins.
</P>
<P>
   (Putnam, $25.95.) Tracking an assassin who threatens
</P>
<P>
   the stability of the British and American governments.
</P>
<P>
   13. THE GIRLS' GUIDE TO HUNTING AND FISHING, by Melissa
</P>
<P>
   Bank. (Viking, $23.95.) The progress of a young New York
</P>
<P>
   woman through the terrain of sex and love.
</P>
<P>
   14. BEYOND THE GREAT SNOW MOUNTAINS, by Louis L'Amour.
</P>
<P>
   (Bantam, $16.95.) Ten short stories ranging from
</P>
<P>
   the Old West to Hollywood to Siberia.
</P>
<P>
   15.(x) DANGEROUS KISS, by Jackie Collins. (Simon &AMP;
</P>
<P>
   Schuster, $25.) Lucky Santangelo copes with many problems
</P>
<P>
   as she tracks down the killer of a member of her family.
</P>
<P>
   16.(x) A GOD IN RUINS, by Leon Uris. (HarperCollins, $26.)
</P>
<P>
   On his way to the White House, Quinn Patrick O'Connell
</P>
<P>
   discovers a secret that imperils his political future.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NONFICTION &LR;
</P>
<P>
   1. THE GREATEST GENERATION, by Tom Brokaw. (Random
</P>
<P>
   House, $24.95.) The lives of men and women who came
</P>
<P>
   of age during the Depression and World War II.
